Uses of Package
com.here.android.mpa.routing

  • Packages that use com.here.android.mpa.routing 
    Package Description
    com.here.android.mpa.customlocation
    This package provides classes and interfaces that support custom location searches.
    com.here.android.mpa.guidance
    This package includes classes, interfaces, and enumerations related to guidance and turn-by-turn navigation, used by other packages in the APIs for Android SDK.
    com.here.android.mpa.mapping
    The mapping package provides classes, interfaces, and enumerations that display an interactive map, and related functionality that allows your application to create and add map content.
    com.here.android.mpa.routing
    This package provides classes, interfaces, and enumerations for route calculation and route description (directions).
    com.here.android.mpa.streetlevel
    The streetlevel package provides classes, interfaces, and enumerations that display an interactive StreetLevelFragment.
    com.here.android.mpa.venues3d
    This package provides facilities to search and display objects representing three-dimensional views of venues.

    RouteManager
    Deprecated. 
    As of SDK 3.2. Use an SDK component which implements the Router interface. For core routing types (Car, Truck, Pedestrian) the appropriate class is CoreRouter. For Public Transit routing the appropriate class is UMRouter.
    RouteManager.Error
    Deprecated. 
    As of SDK 3.2. Use RoutingError.
    RouteManager.Listener
    Deprecated. 
    As of SDK 3.2. Use CoreRouter.Listener.

    RouteOptions.TimeType
    Ways that the time can be specified.
    RouteOptions.TransportMode
    Represents values describing different mode of transportation a person will be using.
    RouteOptions.TruckType
    Defines names for different types of trucks.
    RouteOptions.TunnelCategory
    Specify the ADR tunnel category to restrict the truck route to.
    RouteOptions.Type
    Represents different types of routing, such as by speed or by distance.

    Router.Listener

    This is the definition of the RouteResult class.
    RouteResult.ViolatedOption
    These are options which may be ignored by the routing engine; in such cases a list of violated options is returned in the listener's on_end() method.
